Chapter: Closure In Record

 Probe: does bootstrap2 compile a record field holding a closure
 that captures a local? This is the real shape the builtin dispatch
 table would need if any emit-wrapper is a lambda.

Section: Types
  Box = record {
    label : Text,
    apply : Integer -> Text
  }

Section: Builder
  make-box : Text -> Integer -> Box
  make-box (lbl) (offset) =
   Box {
    label = lbl,
    apply = \x -> lbl ++ ":" ++ integer-to-text (x + offset)
   }

Section: Entry Point
  main : [Console] Nothing
  main =
   let b1 = make-box "a" 10
   in let b2 = make-box "b" 100
   in do
    print-line (b1.apply 3)
    print-line (b2.apply 3)
